		"description": "<p>Bundles of rough lumber turn to timeless furniture and sturdy construction under your careful lathe. You gain proficiency with carpenter's tools, or if you are already proficient you gain an expertise die instead. As an action, you can artfully sabotage an adjacent wooden device or vehicle using your carpenter&rsquo;s tools. Examples include jamming a door shut, freeing a wagon&rsquo;s wheel, or disabling a ship&rsquo;s rudder. The Engineering check required to undo these sabotages and the combat maneuver DC to avoid them if the device or vehicle is attended is equal to your passive Intelligence carpenter&rsquo;s tools score. In addition, you have advantage on checks made to create schematics for wooden items.</p>",
